"{\"uid\": \"oann.com-newsroom-2-male-boxers-previously-barred-from-womens-events-will-fight-in-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"OAN StaffJames Meyers11:33 AM - Wednesday, July 31, 2024  Two male boxers who were disqualified from competing with women at a global event last year have been allowed to fight in the Paris Olympics, the International Olympic Committee confirmed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 3, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/One_America_News_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"OAN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/One_America_News_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/One_America_News_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"two trans athletes allowed to compete in Olympics BOXING \\ud83e\\udd4athe international olympics committee has cleared two trans athletes ( Imane Khalif and Lin Yu-Ting) to compete in boxing despite failing the required gender tests put in place by the boxing federation.\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"the move has\\u2026pic.twitter.com/vacDZ0Bumv  Imane Khelif of Algeria and Lin Yu\\u2011ting of Taiwan failed to meet gender eligibility tests at the Women's World Boxing Championships in New Delhi last year, causing the males to be disqualified.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.999999520532698, \"rank\": 4.3900323499359085e-07, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9966728692341246, \"rank\": 0.003259549331676506, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.999999999438387, \"rank\": 5.580691446029528e-10, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 685, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"score\": 0.9998378587438543, \"rank\": 0.00016114151879844605, \"text\": \"New Delhi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time of their disqualifications, the president of the International Boxing Association (IBA), which governs the World Boxing Championships, alleged that the boxers' chromosome tests came back as XY (women typically have two X chromosomes, while men typically have an X and a Y chromosome).\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8510269401268503e-17, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9973494857314037, \"rank\": 0.0024066002249330453, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.777088121899103, \"rank\": 0.2868553045107047, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Based on DNA tests, we identified a number of athletes who tried to trick their colleagues into posing as women,\\\" the association's president, Umar Kremlev, told Russia's Tass news agency at the time.\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1187, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"score\": 0.9999996524227903, \"rank\": 3.425748717128647e-07, \"text\": \"Umar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\"}, {\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9998885756185167, \"rank\": 9.184594604300642e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tass news agency\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"According to the results of the tests, it was proved that they have XY chromosomes.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Such athletes were excluded from competition.\\\"\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the two have been cleared to compete in the women's 66-kilogram and women's 57-kilogram matches in Paris this week, the IOC confirmed in an email Tuesday.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995672431877, \"rank\": 4.327570136513661e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1254594793265426e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ruling received backlash from female boxer and Australian captain Caitlin Parker, who said this could be very dangerous for the sport.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.993964728433759, \"rank\": 0.005295476300268387, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Parker\", \"score\": 0.9999997772802337, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caitlin Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Parker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not agree with them being allowed to compete in sport, especially combat sports,\\\" Parker said.\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloysius_Parker\", \"score\": 0.946543482908063, \"rank\": 0.05647524133644409, \"text\": \"Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloysius_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloysius_Parker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It can be incredibly dangerous.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not agree with it,\\\" she continued.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not like I have not sparred men before.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But you know it can be dangerous for combat sports and it should be seriously looked into.\\\"\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yes, biologically \\u2026 genetically they are going to have more advantages and in combat sports it can be dangerous,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I really hope the organizations get their act together so that boxing can continue to be at the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Women's boxing was only introduced in 2012 and I want to see it for the next 100, 200 years to come,\\\" she concluded.\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Khelif is slated to compete against Italy's Angela Carinin on Thursday, and Lin is set to fight against Uzbekistan's Sitora Turdibekova on Friday.\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.8012928517699444, \"rank\": 0.1607998419017676, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999916994966, \"rank\": 5.461375344939538e-09, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay informed!\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Receive breaking news blasts directly to your inbox for free.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe here.https://www.oann.com/alerts    What do YOU think?\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Click here to jump to the comments!\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this post!\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Accessibility Tools\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": []}]}"